\par
\b 7. Practical Conclusion\par
\b0
The repository did not become locally runnable by export alone. It became locally runnable because the missing Supabase-dependent pieces were recovered through staged schema patches, function parity work, authorization hardening, local setup scripts, governance extensions, and packaging/documentation for customer-managed deployment.\par
\par
\b 8. Recommended Onboarding Note For Future Programmers\par
\b0
If a future developer needs to rebuild or troubleshoot the local stack, they should not assume that the raw Supabase export is sufficient. They should start from the local runbook, apply the bootstrap SQL assets in order, verify frontend contract coverage, validate role behavior, and use the schema dump only as a reference snapshot, not as the only recovery mechanism.\par
